<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 09 at 5:02PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...SLIPPERY ROADS FOR THE EVENING COMMUTE WITH BRIEF HEAVY SNOW
RATES...
Steady snowfall continues for the evening commute for much of the
area with temperatures in the upper 20s to mid 30s. Moderate to
occasionally heavy snowfall rates will result in accumulations
of 1 to 2 inches inch on roads and other surfaces causing slippery
travel conditions. As temperatures continue to warm this evening,
snow will transition to rain at lower elevations, and at higher
elevations tonight.</description>
